======================================================================
ANALYSIS: ALL-CONFLICTING THRESHOLD
======================================================================

At n=3: max 1 cycle (one 3-cycle), alpha_2=0 trivial
At n=4: max 2 3-cycles on 4 vertices, always share 2+ vertices
At n=5: 5-cycles enter. 10 3-cycles + 1-3 5-cycles for regular
At n=6: More cycles, disjoint pairs become easier

KEY QUESTION: Is alpha_2=0 achievable for alpha_1 >= 3?
If NOT: then the all-conflicting property is bounded by alpha_1 <= 2
for ALL n, meaning H=7 is the FIRST impossible (a1,0) value
and all (a1,0) with a1 >= 3 are impossible.
